Part 1 – Development Project (50%)
Your task is to develop a CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) 
Market Place web application using PHP and Symfony. Your 
implementation should utilise all relevant framework features as 
covered in the workshops and follow best development practice.
Your application should include user management, allowing users to 
register new accounts and log in/out.
As core features your application should allow the management of 
adverts. Adverts need to contain a title, description, and the user
who created it. For higher marks this may be extended to include 
further information such as price, location and (managed) 
categories.
Anyone (i.e. no user account required) should be able to browse 
existing adverts. There should be a list view of all advert titles
(potentially paginated for higher marks) as well as individual pages
showing full advert details when clicking on a title in the list view.
Logged-in users should be able to create new adverts as well as edit 
and delete their own existing adverts. For higher marks you may 
consider implementing additional roles (such as moderator and 
admin where moderators might be allowed to edit/delete anyone’s 
adverts and admins might be allowed to promote/demote
moderators and delete user accounts).
Adequate application security should be put in place utilising the 
framework’s authentication and authorisation mechanisms.
For higher marks you may consider additional features that enhance 
the application and demonstrate independent research and a 
deeper understanding of the used technologies (such as the ability 
to upload and display images for adverts)